              "selectedReview": {
                "nickName": "Lauren",
                "regionCode": "",
                "content": "Booked this trip for my finances birthday. \nThe hotel is outdated which we were aware of and no issues there but if you\u2019re looking for something modern it\u2019s not the place for you. The lift doors were very sticking and didn\u2019t seem to open properly and had a bad smell to them. \n\nChecked in ok, went to our room which had the heating on full blast and the temp was showing at 39c. We tried to open the window but it was held closed by just a screw. \n\nThe bed was very comfy to sleep on but we only stayed one night so wasn\u2019t too bad. \n\nThe next morning we were disturbed by housekeeping entering our room at 8am saying hello then quickly exiting and then hoovering the corridors banging the walls and our door. We told reception about this but was greeted by a rude member of staff who pointed to another lady then walked off. The lady behind the desk said she\u2019ll talk to housekeeping again so sounds like this happens a lot.\n\nWe then decided to go for breakfast to be told it was \u00a315 each! Apparently when you check in you can buy breakfast at a discounted rate of \u00a312.50 but no one told us or offered this at check in. We decided to go elsewhere for breakfast. \nAll in all we had a good trip to London but will not recommend this hotel or ever be returning again. I wish I had spent a bit more and gone to a better hotel.",
