              "selectedReview": {
                "nickName": "HUI MIN",
                "regionCode": "",
                "content": "We had a lovely stay at St Giles, London. \nWell located hotel, near to Tottenham Court Road Station, bus stops, supermarkets, shops, eateries, theatres etc. From Heathrow Airport, we took the Elizabeth line to Tottenham Court Road Station and hotel was just a short walk away. The British museum was also nearby.\nHotel staff were friendly, helpful and efficient. As we arrived rather early, Nikki helped us to secure a room earlier than official check in time, so that we can put our luggages and rest.\nThe concierge guys were great, giving advice on how best to get to our destination. The Chinese gentleman, sorry, I didn't get his name, even helped me with my Bolt app bookings!\nWe booked 2 new twin rooms. Although they were small, they were sufficient for 2 pax in each room. All amenities that we needed were available and rooms were cleaned thoroughly when we returned from our sightseeing. There was no air conditioner in the rooms but weather was great, so we had no issues.\nThe breakfast served was excellent, with a wide variety. \nGood choice for our short stay in London.",
                "rating": 5,
                "avatarImgUrl": "https://ak-d.tripcdn.com/target/1i52g12000dex1hwn04E3.jpg",
                "reviewDate": "2024-06-04 21:41:12"
              },
              "selectedReviewList": [
                {
                  "nickName": "HUI MIN",
                  "regionCode": "",
                  "content": "We had a lovely stay at St Giles, London. \nWell located hotel, near to Tottenham Court Road Station, bus stops, supermarkets, shops, eateries, theatres etc. From Heathrow Airport, we took the Elizabeth line to Tottenham Court Road Station and hotel was just a short walk away. The British museum was also nearby.\nHotel staff were friendly, helpful and efficient. As we arrived rather early, Nikki helped us to secure a room earlier than official check in time, so that we can put our luggages and rest.\nThe concierge guys were great, giving advice on how best to get to our destination. The Chinese gentleman, sorry, I didn't get his name, even helped me with my Bolt app bookings!\nWe booked 2 new twin rooms. Although they were small, they were sufficient for 2 pax in each room. All amenities that we needed were available and rooms were cleaned thoroughly when we returned from our sightseeing. There was no air conditioner in the rooms but weather was great, so we had no issues.\nThe breakfast served was excellent, with a wide variety. \nGood choice for our short stay in London.",
