              "selectedReview": {
                "nickName": "Guest User",
                "regionCode": "",
                "content": "On arrival we were given a nice double room - plenty of space, clean with a well furnished bathroom.  After about half an hour we realised the heating in the room wasn't working so I called down to reception. Within 5 mins of calling, a lovely young member of staff came up to look at it. After another 5 mins or so he had upgraded us to an executive room on the same floor which was huge! He even offered to help us move our cases etc to the new room. We were also given complimentary vouchers for drinks and coffees.  The breakfast buffet had plenty of choice so all good with us.   Cannot fault the customer care but there were a couple of small things that weren't great - the toilet in the second room didn't flush well at all but after being upgraded we weren't going to make an issue of it so said nothing  Only other thing was the lack of light in the room - we had a side room so no natural light got in. There were a couple of lamps on the desk but far too dull - not great when trying to do hair and make up for a wedding!   All in all we had an enjoyable stay at the Jury's Manchester and would stay again.",
