              "selectedReview": {
                "nickName": "Guest User",
                "regionCode": "",
                "content": "The location of this hotel is perfect. A few minutes walk up James Street towards all the shopping, cinema, restaurants in Liverpool One as well as the rest of the city and if you go the opposite way you are at Albert Dock. There is a Weatherspoons directly across the road serving food and drinks too   The whole building is clean and modern.   Unfortunately, we found the beds to be uncomfortable. So hard to get a good night's sleep.  Some floors seem to be used for emergency housing, a lot of people just hanging around and bringing old bikes up the lifts. Whole building heating is set really high.  Drinks from the fridge are expensive \u20ac5 for a water and pepsi. No parking (you have to park at Liverpool One) so if it's raining you will be soaked by the time you walk back to the hotel. It's not cheap either \u00a316 pound from 10pm -10am (off peak) and that included a \u20ac30 off voucher from the hotel.   I would still use this hotel but probably more as a solo traveller.  ",
