              "selectedReview": {
                "nickName": "BluePieEric",
                "regionCode": "",
                "content": "Convenient Location, but Room Size and Amenities Could Be Better. I recently stayed at the Travelodge Chinatown in Kuala Lumpur. The hotel\u2019s location is excellent~ just a short walk to the Pasar Seni station and close to the well-known tourist spot, Petaling Street. This made it convenient for us to explore nearby eateries and attractions.\n\nHowever, there were a few downsides. The rooms are quite small, and we noticed some ant activity. If you\u2019re not bothered by these issues, it\u2019s worth considering. Keep in mind that the hotel is basic, suitable mainly for budget travelers looking for a short stay. The breakfast buffet provided by the hotel was simple and not very tasty; I recommend exploring nearby food options instead. I hope this review helps! \ud83d\ude0a",
