            "content": "I stayed here for 3 days while traveling to the Tiger Valley and Jade Dragon Snow Mountain.\n\nIt is located right next to Lijiang Ancient City, and the entrance to the hostel is controlled by a barrier, so outside vehicles cannot enter and exit, so it is very quiet (people can enter and exit freely).\n\nThe young lady boss was very kind and managed clearly, so there was no inconvenience at all.\n\nDue to the nature of traveling to Lijiang, if you go out early in the morning and return at night, or stay overnight at a guest house at the Tiger Valley, there is no place to store your luggage, but I think it is a really cost-effective place to stay while traveling to the Tiger Valley and Jade Dragon Snow Mountain.\n\nNext time, I want to go to Shangri-la, but even then, I plan to stay here for a day and then move on to Shangri-la.\nIt's like old age:)",
